37 &\equiv 1\pmod{12}\\
49 &\equiv 1\pmod{12} \\
14 &\equiv 2\pmod{12}
\end{align*}then therefore, $37+49+14 \equiv1+1+2 \equiv \boxed{4}\pmod{12}$.

